verses.roman:
guṇḍicā-mandire gelā, kibā narendrere?
caṭaka-parvate gelā, kibā koṇārkere?'

synonyms: guṇḍicā-mandire—to the Guṇḍicā temple; gelā—has gone; kibā—or; narendrere—to the Narendra Lake; caṭaka-parvate—to Caṭaka-parvata; gelā—has gone; kibā—or; koṇārkere—to the Koṇārka temple.
translation: "Perhaps He went to the Guṇḍicā temple, or to Lake Narendra, or to the Caṭaka-parvata. Maybe He went to the temple at Koṇārka."
